      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TARBHACH (8) is a talented type and proved too strong last time to win by one length at this track in a handy 30.40 beating Aston Machine. The form from his last run is stacking up nicely. Can measure up again. BELAIR BRINDLE (1) hasn't been far away, finishing in the money twice in a row including last time in a Grade 5 at this track over 525m. This looks easier and expected to improve sharply. ZIPPING KOSTER (2) doesn't show much early dash but winds into her races and is overdue, hitting the line hard to place latest (31.04) in a Grade 4/5 at this track and making it three minors in a row. Solid record at the distance winning two races. Ready to find winning form. SMALLER ACTS (4) boasts a solid strike-rate over this trip.",
